quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,"Ta seen meem."
  26,2,"These are the verses of the manifest Book."
  26,3,"Seemingly you are going to let yourself collapse in grief because they do not believe."
  26,4,"If We so will, We can send down to them a sign from the sky before which their necks will stay bent in submission."
  26,5,"And there comes to them no new message from the Rahman, but they become averse to it."
  26,6,"Thus they rejected (the Truth); so soon will come to them the real descriptions of what they used to ridicule."
  26,7,"Have they not looked at the earth, how many of the noble pairs (of vegetation) We have caused to grow therein?"
  26,8,"Surely, in this there is a sign, and most of them are not to believe"
  26,9,"And surely your Lord is the Mighty, the Merciful."
  26,10,"And (remember) when your Lord called Musa saying, "Go to the transgressing people,"
  26,11,"the people of Fir` aun (the Pharaoh). Do they not fear Allah?""
  26,12,"He (Musa) said, "My Lord, I fear they will belie me."
  26,13,"And my heart gets straitened and my tongue is not fluent; so send for Harun."
  26,14,"And they have (made) a charge of offence against me and I fear they will kill me;""
  26,15,"He (Allah) said, Never! So go, both of you, with Our signs. We are with you, listening."
  26,16,"So, the two of you reach the Fir` aun and say, 'We both are messengers of the Lord of all the worlds,"
  26,17,"(sent with the message) that you must send the children of Isra it with us""
  26,18,"He (the Pharaoh) said, 'Did we not nourish you among us as a child? And you remained among us for years,"
  26,19,"and you did that deed of yours which you did while you were among the ungrateful."